description:
We have an exciting opportunity for a
 **Lead Solution Architect** 
 , fluent speaker in Swedish, to join our Central European Presales Team. As a key member of our organization, you will play a vital role in defining and delivering major technical projects, strategies, and architectures.










 Your expertise will enable us to develop integrated solutions that meet our current and future business needs. We are looking for someone who not only understands our customers' business and commercial issues, but also provides valuable insights to drive innovation.










**Responsibilities:** 










 · Lead a talented design team: You will have the opportunity to manage and inspire a large design team, guiding them to deliver exceptional results;




 · Strategic project delivery: Define and communicate high-level structures to facilitate the design and development of integrated solutions. This includes identifying areas where service, process, organization, and operating models need improvement, in addition to technology components. You will ensure that agreed requirements, such as the automation of business processes, are met and provide options and considerations for key business decisions;




 · Influential decision-making: Shape technical proposals to align with customer needs and make necessary solution/service trade-offs. Your expertise and strategic insights will influence the approach to whole classes of business and drive the development of new offerings;




 · Collaborate with customers: Work closely with our customers to understand their business strategies and develop IT strategies and architecture for significant areas of their operations. Your input will be crucial in aligning their goals with our solutions;




 · Design and requirements management: Collaborate with your team to define customer requirements and produce comprehensive designs. You will establish high-level design criteria for major solutions and ensure that design control is maintained throughout the implementation process;




 · Thought leadership: Share your expertise by communicating the impact of emerging technologies on our customers and our business. You will have the opportunity to present your insights to senior-level customers and internal stakeholders, contributing to our thought leadership in the industry;




 · Knowledge sharing: Foster a culture of knowledge sharing by contributing to our company's knowledge repositories and participating in relevant events. Your valuable additions to our knowledge base will benefit both our team and our customers.










**Qualifications:** 










 · Proven experience: You have a track record of successfully managing and delivering large-scale technical projects, strategies, and architectures. Your expertise has influenced investment decisions and shaped successful proposals;




 · Strong leadership skills: You are a natural leader who can inspire and guide a diverse team of professionals. Your strategic mindset allows you to drive innovation and influence decision-making at a senior level;




 · Business acumen: You possess a deep understanding of customers' business and commercial issues. You can effectively translate their needs into IT strategies and architecture that align with their goals;




 · Technical expertise: You have a strong technical background in workplace solution design. Your knowledge of emerging technologies enables you to provide valuable insights and thought leadership;




 · Excellent communication: You excel in communicating complex concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences. Your ability to deliver compelling presentations and "white papers" is essential in Swedish and in English.
















 If you are a motivated architect with a passion for delivering innovative solutions and driving business success, we want to hear from you. Join our team and be part of an organization that values your expertise and offers opportunities for professional growth. Apply now to make a significant impact as an Lead Solution Architect.
















*For the consultant/employee selected for the role, checks of public registers and records relating to financial and legal status will be conducted. By submitting an application, the candidate consents to such checks being carried out.*

**JOB SUMMARY** 




 As an HR Generalist, you will be responsible for supporting local HR operations in Sweden. This includes ensuring the compliant management of payroll, employee lifecycle activities, general services, and industrial relations matters for the project.










 You will ensure full compliance with Company standards, Client requirements, and applicable local legislation throughout construction and commissioning activities. This role will be to play a key part in a Bio-Energy Carbon Capture and Storage project.
















**RESPONSIBILITIES** 




 • Act as focal point for payroll processing, coordinating with external payroll providers, internal finance teams, line managers and employees;










 • Collect, validate and submit payroll inputs (i.e. new hires, leavers, absences, overtime, allowances, benefits in kind, expenses claims, timesheets);










 • Assist in the management of tax registrations, social security obligations and onboarding documentation (both locals and posted workers);










 • Support the HR Manager in industrial relations matters, interfacing with trade unions, employers’ associations and external labor consultants;










 • Act as a key HR interface for subcontractors on industrial relations and labor compliance topics;










 • Support implementation and monitoring of applicable collective agreements;










 • Ensure compliance with Swedish labor law (Working Hours Act, holidays, sick leave, termination rules, etc.);










 • Coordinate general services for local and posted worker staff (office facilities, access badges, IT equipment, onboarding logistics);










 • Support mobilization and demobilization processes for locally hired employees;










 • Coordinate with Site Management on administrative and workforce support needs;










 • Support accommodation, commuting or welfare-related logistics;
















**REQUIREMENTS** 




 • Five years of HR operations experience in Sweden.










 • Demonstrated expertise in payroll coordination and liaising with external payroll providers in Sweden.










 • Familiarity with industrial relations and collective bargaining environments within Sweden is required.










 • Experience managing posted workers in construction, engineering, or industrial projects in a multinational setting is highly desirable.










 • Solid knowledge of Swedish labor law and Industrial relations system.










 • Familiarity with trade unions (e.g. IF Metall, Unionen) and employers’ associations










 • Move comfortably among all other common MS Office applications (including AI apps)










 • Swedish and English proficient
